{"attack":true,"case":"The target violates std-crit-design clause (1): the proposed mechanism does not state the divergence condition in the required measurable quantities as a coherent, self-consistent model. The prose mechanism claims that at p=0.75, k=5, 'even perfect recall leaves 0-1 wrong candidates but only 1 correct, so filtering cannot create a correct plurality — at best a tie.' This is arithmetically incoherent: at k=5, p=0.75 implies ~3.75 wrong and ~1.25 correct on average, so with perfect recall (phi=1.0) flagging all wrong candidates, ~1.25 correct survive unflagged while ~0 wrong survive, yielding a correct plurality — the exact opposite of the claimed 'at best a tie.' The mechanism thus misstates the divergence condition it purports to specify. More critically, the target's central forbidden case (p=0.65, phi=0.75, psi=0.35, k=5, harness accuracy NOT at least 8pp above SC) is directly contradicted by the target's own scope and claim: the scope lists the strict-win regime as covering 'p in (0.5, 0.8) at k=5' with 'phi > 0.6' and 'psi in (0.2, 0.5),' and p=0.65/phi=0.75/psi=0.35 sits squarely inside all three ranges. The mechanism text then asserts that at p=0.55, phi=0.7, psi=0.3 (strictly weaker parameters than the forbidden test point on every axis), the harness 'elects the correct answer.' If the harness succeeds at the weaker neighboring point, the forbidden case at the stronger point (higher p but still well within the claimed band, higher phi, higher psi) should not be a forbidden failure — yet it is registered as one. The target cannot simultaneously claim the strict-win band is p∈(0.5,0.8) with phi>0.6 and psi>0.3 and forbid failure at an interior point (p=0.65, phi=0.75, psi=0.35) that satisfies all three inequalities. This is not a boundary test; it is a direct self-contradiction between the scope/claim and the forbidden case, violating the requirement that the divergence condition be stated in consistent measurable quantities.","counterexample":[{"p":0.65,"k":5,"phi":0.75,"psi":0.35,"note":"Interior point of claimed strict-win band (p∈(0.5,0.8), phi>0.6, psi∈(0.2,0.5)) registered as forbidden failure, contradicting the scope and the mechanism's success claim at the weaker neighboring point (p=0.55, phi=0.7, psi=0.3)"}]}